title: Old Grange button font
content:
This appears to be two different fonts. Help identifying please?

| --- | --- |

author: trampanzee

comments.content:
"I'M PROUD TO BE A": I see [Trade Gothic](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/linotype/trade-gothic) Condensed Bold (#20?) may be manually rounded?  
"GRANGER": alternatives [Silverstone Woodtype](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/thometz/silvertone-woodtype), [Reforma Grotesk](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/paratype/reforma-grotesk-bold-e), [Rama Gothic](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/flat-it/rama-gothic), [Akzidenz Grotesk](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/berthold/akzidenz-grotesk-be) Condensed Bold, [Block Gothic](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/redrooster/block-gothic-rr), [Helvetica](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/linotype/helvetica) Compressed, [Hector](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/dsgnhaus/hector), [Smart Sans](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/mti/smart-sans), [Plakette](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/ef-typeshop/plakette) (~Inserat), [Sorren Ex](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/reserves/sorren-ex), [Railroad Gothic](http://web.archive.org/web/20140823105835/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/redrooster/railroad-gothic-rr)
